<paragraph id="8BB58B04FFA7754EFCE4FF1AFC1887A5" blockId="11.[829,1444,199,801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFCE4FF1AFC0786A8" box="[854,954,199,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Remarks</emphasis>
: Corresponds to the species group B of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AF087FFA7754EFC8FFF38FBEC868F" authority="(Hansen, 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[829,1105,229,251]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Lucifer" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFC8FFF38FC33868E" box="[829,910,229,250]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Lucifer</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9BF6F5FFA7754EFC11FF38FBF4868F" author="Hansen HJ" box="[931,1097,229,251]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref9485" refString="Hansen HJ. (1919). The Sergestidae of the Siboga expedition. 1 - 65." type="book chapter" year="1919">Hansen, 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The genus is easily distinguished from its sister genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AF087FFA7754EFB07FED9FABB876D" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1205,1286,260,281]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Lucifer" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFB07FED9FABB876D" box="[1205,1286,260,281]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Lucifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by mediumsized, subcylindrical eyestalks and eyes that are not sexually dimorphic. Males also differ in having a nearly straight posterior ventral process on the sixth abdominal somite and in the shape and armature of the sheath and processus ventralis of the petasma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB58B04FFA7754EFCE4FE07FC4A8576" blockId="11.[829,1444,199,801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFCE4FE07FC70879B" box="[854,973,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Etymology</emphasis>
: From the Hebrew ‘ba’al’ meaning ‘lord’ and ‘z’bhubh’ meaning ‘fly’. We chose the Old English transliteration because it is shorter than the Greek ‘beelzeboub’. ‘Belzebub’ is sometimes referred to as another name for the devil, so by this name we allude to the close relationship between this genus and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AF087FFA7754EFB3DFD4CFB5D84D2" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1167,1248,657,678]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Lucifer" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFB3DFD4CFB5D84D2" box="[1167,1248,657,678]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Lucifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another wellknown synonym of the word ‘devil’ (but note that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AF087FFA7754EFC8FFD13FC338497" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[829,910,718,739]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Lucifer" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFC8FFD13FC338497" box="[829,910,718,739]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Lucifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually was intended to mean ‘light-bearer’ in this context).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB58B04FFA7754EFCE4FCD6FA278555" blockId="11.[829,1444,199,801]" box="[854,1434,779,801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B97E5716FFA7754EFCE4FCD6FC628554" box="[854,991,779,800]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Distribution</emphasis>
: Neritic genus, panoceanic distribution.
</paragraph>
